info.value: There are surprisingly few north americans and europeans in the same clusters. I have just realized there is a person category, which does, in fact, answer my question about how to tell if someone is a person.  It's interesting how arbitrary the people in the matrix appear to be, with so many not having more than one or two interactions.

info.value: Jeffery has the most followers but relatively few tweets. The is also only one single user from South America which seems odd. Institutions generally have fewer tweets and followers than people. Account age is not necessarily correlated with the number of tweets or followers. North Americans also seem to have greater tweets and followers on average than Europeans. There is only one cluster.
